# Representative op / position parametrize lists.
#
# The wide-signal cross-engine family tests use combinatorial parametrize
# matrices (outer_op × inner_op × position × widths).  The wide emitter
# dispatches bitwise ops (&, |, ^) through a single word-parallel path and
# arithmetic ops (+, -) through carry/borrow add/neg.  One representative
# from each dispatch class is sufficient to cover the codegen paths; the
# previous fully-crossed matrices generated thousands of unique DUTs (each
# a unique Cython compile + cached .pyd → tens of GB of .cycache).
#
# To restore full op-cross coverage temporarily, swap these names to point
# at the _FULL_* variants below.  See ``notes/known_issues.md`` for context.
# ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
